A randomized double blind clinical trial to assess efficacy of leflunomide in treatment of refractory juvenile idiopathic arthritis.

 Patients are randomly divided into two groups.

 In group 1 leflunomide and in group 2 placebos will be added to conventional treatment for three months.

 therapeutic responses will be evaluated by ACRpedi (American College of Rheumatology Pediatric) scores every 4 weeks.

